caption: This restaurant has a great reputation. The service, ambiance and complimentary valet parking were great. The service was quick and friendly, I ordered a burger, it looked delicious. Flavor was plain and unimpressive.

Excellent! They have a limited menu right now, but the Enchiladas and Fajitas were very good. The Sangria was very tasty. The staff all wore masks & the dining area was spaced out for social distancing. Highly recommend!
This place is great.  Their menu is very simple and the bar service was great.  We had a bunch of appetizers.
Exceptional service and great staff! The okra, spinach and curry potatoes and channa were on point along with the paratha 🥰
Delicious Guyanese Chinese Food
Good patties, and good fishcakes!
Got delivery through Seamless. The food is delicious! Love the pineapple pastry. Their fried chicken is very crispy. Jerk chicken and fried rice plate is delicious and also a huge serving.

This is guyanese food made with love.  I had recently came here for dinner for the first time. I didn't have any long lines or rude service, I actually had the quite opposite experience.  When I had walked in I was probably one of the only ones inside the restaurant and the server who was helping me was very nice and attentive.  I had ordered the oxtail with rice.  The oxtail was beautifully seasoned and was super tender and the sauce had accompanied the rice very well.  I had also ordered the roti .  The roti itself was definitely worth it -it was nice to have on the side to soak up all the sauces.

"Food is really flavorful, the portions are great also. I'm horrible at taking pictures but Hubby got the curried goat with white rice and roti. I got curried chicken with white rice and roti. The roti portions are amazing for the price.The environment is a little chaotic, but hey, I can understand why, the food is awesome. If you're looking for authentic guyanese food, this place is it!"

Ever since experiencing my first Roti in Queens and finding this gem in Richmond Hils (they're on my way home from a lot of trips) it has been a MUST STOP. The other foods look good, they really do, BUT the chinese food is my fav..
Far better than Kaieteur! The chicken over rice is yummy

"This is a great restaurant on Jamaica Ave. You would probably pass this place if you didn't know what they had. It is very much so underrrated.  If you have never had roti, this would be a good place to start. It's very flavorful and it gives your all the tastes of the West Indian culture. There are also options on the menu if you don't want roti.  I had the shrimp roti and it was very good. It was more zesty than spicy."

While visiting New York recently a friend recommened this resturant. The service is equal to that of the islanders at an incredibly reasonable price. We have yet to find another place that has good tasting curry or "island service"

"I was really happy to find a local restaurant that offered the delicious cuisine of the West Indies. I have a fondness for curry with roti. I was pleasantly greeted by smiles and quick service. The food is fresh and delicious. The food has plenty of spices and is delicious.  Definitely will be returning in the near future!"

I've been coming here since they opened, and they have really good food. Every time I come I get chicken curry cause I have yet to find another place in town that does it as well as them. As a guyanese, their food is really good.

"  Palm Court Halal offers a full range of Rotis and curries in a pleasant environment. It's counter service, but very efficient and well-staffed. I'm a big fan of goat roti, but the channa and the chicken are also good.  I suggest getting the roti separate rather than as a wrap.  The place is spotlessly clean, and there's offer home made drinks. "

"Love this place, I always grab a bag plaintian chips on my way to work THe chips are flavorful and wonderful- extra pepper sauce for the win. Roti is fluffy (plain is better) Goat curry is on point, but make sure to get roti on the side if you're taking it to go or it gets real messy real quick.  "

I love this place!!! Excellent friendly staff you'll ever meet. I stood looking at the menu for a solid 5 minutes, I was at a loss, everything smelled so good. Extremely flavorful and spicy. I ended up ordering the duck curry and roti. I was so happy tried it. The meat was perfectly cooked and jam packed with spices. I really hope you consider going to this place.... I am definitely a regular customer now!!!

My go to place for Guyanese style curry. I've tried a few places listed on Google, but this one takes the crown! My usual order is a takeaway of large curry chicken with roit and 2 beef patty.  The vibe inside feels like I'm back in the islands, with  music playing and amazing staff.

This restaurant is absolutely amazing.  Probably the most understated experience in Queens.  Completely unassuming, but the food itself and the staff will totally blow you away.  I got the Chicken fried Rice and goat curry.  My girlfriend got shrimp curry.  Wow.  Perfect portions, perfect cooking, perfect seasoning.  I can't recommend this spot enough.  So nice to have a good local place for my curry in my area.

What's amazing about this place is that it feels like you're welcomed by a family of Guyanese and they are about to serve you a wild ride.  I had the pleasure of ordering food here after a long work day.Might I say, it's a great tasting food.  I had the curry goat which was probably the softest meat that I have ever had in my life. My girlfriend and best friend had the curry chicken which was definitely blazing. Then ended up getting some pastries.
Was in the area so I tried it out for the first time. Ordered chicken and vegetable lo mein. Service was quick and food was delicious.

Customer service is very friendly here. Nicholas was very easy going and provided outstanding service. Marissa recommended good tips on what to order when I was unsure. It is a good place to get food from if you don't want to make the trip to liberty Avenue. Food taste great too. I'm glad they opened in the area. Dhal purrie taste like home made. Food doesn't have much pepper so just add and taste is just right.
